@*
    Example 8 — Follow the OS `prefers-color-scheme`.

    `DetectFromSystem` makes the FIRST-VISIT default follow the OS colour
    scheme. The component probes `matchMedia("(prefers-color-scheme: dark)")`
    once, during initial value resolution, and maps the answer onto a
    supported slug via the public `ThemeSelect.MatchSystemTheme` helper.

    Detection sits in the middle of the resolution order:

        Value > StorageKey > DetectFromSystem > DefaultValue > "light" > Themes[0]

    so a returning visitor's stored choice always wins over the OS
    preference — detection only decides the first visit. If the OS prefers
    a scheme this control does not offer (e.g. `prefers-color-scheme: dark`
    with no "dark" slug in `Themes`), detection yields nothing and
    resolution falls through to `DefaultValue`.

    Detection is opt-in: without `DetectFromSystem` the media query is
    never probed.

    This mirrors `DetectFromNavigator` on LocaleSelect.
*@

@page "/examples/theme-select/system-preference"
@rendermode InteractiveServer
@using LilyDesignSystem.Blazor.Helpers

<ThemeSelect
    Label="Theme"
    ThemesUrl="/assets/themes/"
    Themes="@(new[] { "light", "dark" })"
    DetectFromSystem="true"
    StorageKey="my-app:theme" />

@*
    Note: `DetectFromSystem` resolves the OS preference ONCE, on first
    render. It does not subscribe to the media query, so it will not
    re-theme the page if the user flips their OS to dark mode while the
    tab is open — that would fight a selection the user made by hand.
    To follow OS changes live, add your own `matchMedia` listener and
    call `SetThemeAsync` from it:

        <ThemeSelect @ref="themeSelect" ... />

        @code {
            private ThemeSelect? themeSelect;
            // ... wire a change listener, then:
            // await themeSelect!.SetThemeAsync(dark ? "dark" : "light");
        }
*@
